Life is way too short to not be living up to your full potential ⚡️
 
For years and years, I thought living up to my potential was based on how many ‘accomplishments’ I had under my belt. That was the life I was accustomed too, and I thought that is what ’successful’ meant! 

But with achieving all these ‘accomplishments’, I was overwhelmed, exhausted, always stressed and felt like I could never catch my breath.

I finally had a moment, broke down in tears and asked myself, Is there anymore to life than just this?! My mind, body and spirit couldn’t take it any longer. Endless to-do list, hundreds of emails, countless hours at work and not feeling fulfilled in return.. this can’t be IT?!

I erased everything on my calendar, and took a new approach. I made sure to implement self care days, balance my work schedule and looked at my intention in how I want to show ups in the world each day. Who am I as an Individual, Mother, Leader,  Teacher, and an Entrepreneur. 

⚡️Who do I want to be in the next 3 years?
⚡️How will I make an impact on others?
⚡️What kind of impact do I want to make?
⚡️What kind of relationships do I want to build in my life and business?

This life moment led me to creating 
✨The Yoga Professional Incubator ✨ 
I felt motivated and inspired to help others, grow their business in the most powerful way possible - with joy and freedom. 

In the Yoga Professional Incubator, we take a look into all aspects of running your business, and most importantly, how to stay true to your authentic self though it all.

Drop a 💗 below for more info on how to join the community of other, heart-centered Yoga Professionals! Enrollment opens next week!

Emerging from a toxic wasteland ☠️

The past year and a half my health started declining:

❌ Brain fog set in
❌ Intense pain in my upper back + neck 
❌ Chronic headaches
❌ Systemic inflammation
❌ Severe gut issues
❌ Joint pain
❌ Numbness in my right arm
❌ A rash that covered my arms, legs, chest
❌ Lesions on my face 
❌ Weird film of fog over my eyes
❌ Anxiety
❌ Depression
❌ Chronic fatigue 

It has been extremely challenging, especially bc for the most part - on the outside I looked completely normal. Over time these symptoms got worse and the feeling inside got worse 😔🥺😢

Doctors visits, blood draws, dermatologists, hormone doctors, optometrists, oncologists, healers = ZERO ANSWERS 0️⃣

For months I’ve felt hopeless, helpless, confused, frustrated, depleted, and exhausted, looking for answers. 

I’ve thought to myself on many occasions, “WTF - How many dragons do I need to slay in this lifetime - over the past decade it feels as though it’s been a TON and I’m tired, can’t things just be easy for a bit”. 

Then I started connecting the dots 😳

My implants (that I never wanted in the first place - post mastectomy in 2018) have been slowly poisoning me ☠️

OMG - F U C K ❌❌❌ 
Breast Implant Illness is REAL

🦄 Found Healing Breast Implant Illness by Nicole on Facebook 
🦄 Connected with other women who were suffering from the same symptoms 
🦄 Connected with women who had suffered from the same symptoms, explanted and HEALED
🦄 Finally felt validated in my experience and felt a sense of hope
🦄 Found an amazing Surgeon that specializes in explants @swistunmd 
🦄 Called on a Friday, and magically got a consult on Monday morning. (A cancellation had just happened 🙏🏼). 
🦄 The consult with @swistunmd was out of this world, educational, supportive, validating, affirming, encouraging and all around amazing. 

I knew in my gut @swistunmd was the one but for due diligence I had other consults with other surgeons, including my original surgeon that did my mastectomy on 2018 and persuaded me to get implants.
